# Allow native install scripts (esbuild, @parcel/watcher) to run during
# ``pnpm install``. Modern pnpm (10+) treats ``ERR_PNPM_IGNORED_BUILDS``
# as fatal in CI environments by default — without this opt-in, the
# admin Docker build fails because esbuild + tailwindcss-cli's
# transitive @parcel/watcher both have postinstall scripts that fetch
# the platform-native binary.
#
# ``onlyBuiltDependencies`` in ``package.json`` is the supported way to
# opt back in but didn't take effect during the Docker build (likely a
# corepack-pulled-pnpm-version vs lockfile-version mismatch). Setting
# the flag here makes the behaviour explicit + stable across pnpm
# versions.
dangerously-allow-all-builds=true
